data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Springfield, MO Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
I walked into Ashley 7/13/24 here in Springfield, MO & worked with a Louis. I straight up told him that we was moving into a house with no furniture & I wanted to make sure everything was IN STOCK before we paid & purchased. I bought a complete living room set with a coffee table & 2 end tables. I also purchased 2 complete bedroom sets. Dressers, night stands & all that. I spent over $9,000 - Paid cash (well on a debit card)...Was told that I would get a text on Sunday letting me know what time they would deliver & set everything up on Tuesday 7/16/24. I got no such text. Texted the sales guy & said he would check on it & send it to me if I didn't receive by the following morning. Still no text received. So instead of calling me & explaining he texts me to say that they actually had 4 pieces of furniture & the rest was in St louis & it would actually be 7/24/24 or later before delivery. Again mind you we asked him several times if it was definitely in stock at the warehouse in Republic, MO. He verified that it was all there. He even brought over other associates to verify. So not only was I lied by the salesman but 2 others also. So we requested the order be cancelled & our money refunded. Was told again by Louis & Jay Wasson the manager that we have our money back in 24 hours. Still have not received my refund. So this morning 7/17/24 we called corporate & per their corporate it will be 7-10 days.... If it is going to be that long...BE HONEST ABOUT IT! Why so long to get back money they received in seconds...So they can put it in Escrow to get the interest off it before it is refunded. They are liars (at least the ones I worked with)..Ended up going to another store & getting all of the same stuff plus a table & 4 chairs & only spent $40 more than I did at Ashley. I will NEVER go there again....Thanks & Have a nice day!!

They open at 10, Monday-Saturday. I got my days mixed up due to my work schedule, so I forgot today was Sunday, which meant they didn’t open until noon. I got off work from the hospital at 7am, ran a few errands, then went to Ashley to wait for them to open. I got there around 9. I took a quick nap, still thinking they opened at 10. Wound up sleeping until about 11. Didn’t see anyone else around, which is when I realized what day it was. So I hung out until they opened. A couple minutes before noon, one of the managers (or so he claimed), Jeff, and another guy, approached my car. Jeff came around to my driver’s side window while the other guy stayed on the passenger side, looking around my backseat. Jeff didn’t ask me anything, like why I had been out there for so long, or anything like that. He told me that the other customers who had shown up *after* me were saying that I was making them uncomfortable. When I tried to explain the situation to him, he raised his hand and talked over me. He accused me of being homeless and just using their lot to sleep in my car. When I told him that I was there to buy a recliner, he raised his hand and talked over me again. He told me they were getting ready to call the cops on me. He told me to leave and go park in the Walmart parking lot instead. But I said “screw that, I’m here to buy something”, so I went in. The salesman JP who sold me my recliner was really nice and helpful, and while I was getting into my car, another manager (I didn’t catch her name) ran out and apologized for Jeff’s rude, unprofessional, childish behavior. Because Jeff is too much of a loser to apologize for himself.

We purchased a lovely front room couch with 6 pieces. The salesman was professional at that point. We could have it delivered on Saturday the but chose the next week on Tuesday the 2nd of July. We didn’t get a call or contact as to the time as we expected. We contacted the store customer service and was told our delivery date was the 5th of July which was not the agreement. We tried to reach our salesman who said the furniture arrived to the store broken and they had to reorder. If that is the truth why were we not contacted but no one bothered knowing this was a 25th wedding anniversary’s surprise for my daughter in law on the 2nd. It took hours of calling to finally reach our salesman. He was not returning our calls. The communication from Ashley salesman was really poor on the verge of rude. We understand things happen but after 2 days of dealing with this we placed one last call and cancelled the entire nearly $5,000 order. When Louis finally returned our call Tuesday we requested a cancellation and repayment in full. He assured us our refund would show in 24 hours so far two days and no credit has been received. Guess what, it has not, nor would I expect any place of business to be able to refund that quickly and see this as just another mistruth. Jackie Mayo order under Rick Mayo my son.i I was involved because I paid for this furniture.

Very unpleased with my most recent experience. Went in for a mattress. Knew our budget before we entered the store. Upon our initial greeting, the salesman brought over the TemperPedic specialist. We immediately made clear we were not interested in that particular brand or the price point. The salesman still made his pitch for the sale and wasted much of our time. We had three children with us ranging from 2 years to 10 years. Even as a potential buyer, we are parents first and had to keep watch over our children. This was not important to the salesman. When we finally made the decision on a different brand, now began the up sale for a very expensive mattress protector and new pillows. Upon our choice to purchase a protector, we were then given instructions on where to sign. During this process it was made clear to me that I had 48 hours to cancel my order. I asked a few questions and continued on. When finished, I grabbed my family and went to our vehicle in a downpour of rain. Along with me, we took the mattress protector as well. After the evening, to take more time to consider the necessity of the protector at the price point we paid, we made the decision to return the protector to save money and buy one for ourselves elsewhere. The next morning I returned to the store to return the protector. I was told by the salesman that had me sign the documents that it could not be returned once it left the store. I said “excuse me?” “You told me we have 48 hours to cancel our order, that’s what I’m doing with this protector.” She then says again that their policy is that it cannot be returned after it leaves the store. At this point I leave very upset. I called the store later that day to speak with a manager about the lack of knowledge about this very unfriendly customer service policy. Of course there was no manager available. I then called the store operations number and voiced my concerns to her. I was told she would email the store directly and have the manager contact me. Three days passed and I never heard a word. I called the store operations line a second time, gave my story again and was once again told I’d be contacted. Same experience. Never received a call, email, text, apology or anything. I am extremely disappointed in my experience. I have spent thousands of dollars spanning over a decade. After this experience, I will no longer spend my hard earned money at Ashley Furniture. They have lost my business over an absurd and unfriendly customer service policy. This needs to be looked into for future customers. I will never go back!

I typically don’t leave reviews however when a person does an outstanding job I feel like it’s only the least I can do to help encourage them to keep helping others and help other customers feel at ease when looking for assistance. I am currently moving and really wanted to vamp up my bed. I had browsed on Ashely’s furniture website but had never stepped foot into their store. To be honest it was a little overwhelming because there was so much to look at and even if I had a general idea of what I wanted it was still a lot to process. That’s when Louis approached me and my sister and really took the time to get to know what my end goal was as far as what I wanted to leave Ashley’s furniture with. From someone that struggles with anxiety and feeling a bit stressed out about purchasing new furniture, Louis was so reassuring and very chill. I loved his ability and knowledge to inform me about the payment plan that I decided to go forward with as well as his overall kindness. Thank you Louis for making this one of the best experiences I’ve had with a sales representative. I most certainly will be coming back and encourage all my friends and family to check out Ashley’s with Louis!

I wish there was a way to give no stars, one star gives them WAY to much credit. Nothing but issues. Picked the couch out and said he has them in stock at the warehouse I can go pick it up tomorrow 8am or the day after for home delivery. Cool I will go rent a trailer and be there at 8am. Not only did they make me pay up front with out seeing it in store. They had the same couch with different material ( different model ). They called me on the way home to tell me my card didn’t go through the system glitched I needed to come back. I have already rented a trailer I said I will come by in the morning and see what’s going on before I pick the couch up. Next morning I get a text “Did that charge ever fall off? “ like ok that’s real professional. Remind you I paid in full, they said I was good gave me paper work and all. Next morning all this is happening remind you before 8am, they text saying will have to refund you. Terrible service. If you think your life is good and want a headache and love dealing with lying salesmen go see my boy LOUIS TAYLOR! He is there 24/7 to ruin your day! Honest review I’m sure it will be removed soon! Ask for LOUIS TAYLOR if he works there save your time and money go elsewhere!

My wife has brain cancer and it has been a brutal fight. A few months ago she was hospitalized twice for both memory loss and loss of strength. When she was discharged from the hospital her mother and sister chipped in to buy her a lift chair to help her regain some level of independence. By the time the chair came in, my mother in law had returned to her home in Colorado. Because the chair was purchased with my mother-in-law's information and the incompetence of the store and their policies it took me over a week and multiple phone calls. Now, only a few months later the chair is having mechanical issues. I called the warranty department and they decided to send parts and then schedule a repair tech once the parts arrived. They arrived yesterday. I called to inform them of their arrival and to make sure nothing happened in error I asked to make sure that the repair tech was sent to the right address here in Missouri where the chair actually is. Well, back down the we can't do anything because someone bought a piece of furniture for someone else rabbit hole we go. This isn't rocket surgery, the chair is here and if there's any question that this is the same chair, I'm certain there's a serial number on it somewhere that can verify it. I never thought I'd see a private company as incompetent as the DMV but here we are, living that dream with Ashley furniture. Also, o don't know if you only have one person that answers the phone with the warranty department or if you just get too many calls because your furniture is junk and breaks that often but you should consider hiring more customer service reps. I started calling yesterday to inform them that the parts were in but twice had to hang up because I had other things to do a d was on hold for over 30 minutes. Today, I was placed in hold for over 47 minutes and when someone finally picked up they were so garbled I had to ask what they said and was immediately put into an automated system asking of I was satisfied with the customer service then hung up on immediately. After another 30 plus minutes of holding on the second call I finally spoke with someone who really couldn't help me much because what she cited as company policy. All of this because someone purchased a chair for someone else. It shouldn't be this complicated.

If there were a zero star, I would give it. More than$1000 for a reclining couch and it didn't last 6 months before becoming so broken it's unusable. This is after our furniture was not delivered on the agreed schedule. After repeated calls to get warranty covered repair over two months, there has still been no repair and no response from Ashley other than they are looking in to it. They have lost us as customer's forever, and we'll be exploring a complaint with the Better Business Bureau. Do yourself a favor and spend more at Haverty's, and make sure the furniture is not made of particle board, aluminum, and pleather like this one. Update 3/6/24: after 4 months of waiting, wrong parts being delivered, Ashley employees telling us if we wanted good furniture we shouldn't buy from Ashley, automated text responses that make no sense, and a couch that gets more broken by the day Ashley informed us that because we moved 4 days ago, months after filing the warranty claim, our warranty is voided. Their last response was, " if there's anything else we can do, don't hesitate to contact us. " No, thank you, you did enough when you ripped us off with crap furniture and refused to honor your warranty. We don't need anymore of your"help". We're off to buy better furniture!

- Bought TV stand & Dining Table/ chairs in store- were told one item would be available on a Monday, next item available on the following Saturday….. and that we’d get a text 48 hours prior to that as a confirmation. - Never got a confirmation text. SO, we called the Friday prior, and they confirmed items would be ready Monday to be picked up. - Called again Saturday to confirm again- they said everything would be ready Monday to be picked up. - Monday- still no text. We looked online and saw the warehouse was closed on Mondays. SO, we called and they confirmed warehouse is closed on Mondays, so we’d need to schedule another day. SO, we scheduled for Tuesday to pick up. - Tuesday my husband shows up at designated time and had to wait an hour for items. He brings it home, and most of the parts to the TV stand are broken/ damaged. He calls immediately and was asked to email photos of all damaged parts- so he did. The lady says it’s too late to submit the warranty tonight, so it would be submitted first thing next morning and that he’d get a call regarding the status…… - Wednesday- NO confirmation call. I called mid day and was told nothing was ever submitted, but that she would submit it while I was on the phone, and was told she’d request an entire replacement for us, and that we’d get a call the next day with status update. - Thursday- NO confirmation call. I called and the guy told me nothing had ever been submitted and requested photos to be sent! I explained my husband already emailed photos 2 days before!! I asked to speak to a supervisor due to multiple mixed messages, he told me a supervisor would be calling me soon. - I waited an hour and called back….. lady told me we had called multiple times and multiple warrantee requests had been submitted and that it takes 72 hours to get an answer on those. - Friday day a supervisor called me, I expressed our horrible customer service experience. He told me we would be getting replacement parts, NOT an entire replacement, despite already being told we’d get an entire replacement… and to call when we received the parts, and that they would then send out a person to put the TV stand together for us. - Saturday we received the replacement parts. - Monday I called to request someone to come put it together and then we were told “they don’t come put it together when we didn’t have it delivered, and it was originally a pick up…. and that we’d have to put it together ourselves.” When my husband opened the boxes they were ALL the WRONG parts AND almost all were damaged!! - What a horrible unprofessional customer service experience this has been!!

About a year ago I purchased 2 sofas and ottomans and a dining room set totaling over $10,000. We all purchased the additional protection plans for each of their sets that we purchased. We discovered that the frame was broken in the oversized ottoman on one of the sofas. I contacted the company we purchased they addition protection through they declined the claim because it was a structure issue that should be covered the the warranty from Ashley Furniture. In October, I contacted Ashley customer service process about the issue and they said someone would contact me with 48 hours to come look at the damage. Several weeks passed with no contact. I contacted them again and was told the claim was closed. I reopened the claim and again was told within 24-28 hours I would be contacted. Again nothing. I tried to contact them through another channel via text. I was asked is we sat on the ottoman. I said, "It was a piece of furniture" and we told that voided the warranty. I've attempted to talk to people higher up the leadership at Ashley and each team has been denied. The customer service process at Ashley is broken. Their warranties are worthless, their follow-up is non existent. I've attempted to resolve this issue in a professional manner but their customer service process does not allow for that to take place. I will never purchase anything from this store again and will encourage others not to purchase anything again. They ottoman was only about $500 of the $10,000 total. They would prefer to lose a customer for life who will influence others not to purchase from their store again as well rather than work to find a solution to their terrible product and even worse costumer service system. Any assistance you can give to correct the issue or help others avoid making the same mistake would be greatly appreciated.

We purchased a table and chair set for 8, as well as a sofa and loveseat. We were told it would take a couple of weeks to be ready for pick up at the distribution center in Republic. We called one week prior to confirm the pick up time, and to our surprise, we were told that we would first need to pay for the items before we could pick them up. The surprising part was the fact that we paid for the items in full when we purchased them in store. After several hours, we were called back and notified that the salesperson who waited on us was new and that she didn’t ‘attach a file’ but that they now could see we did pay for the items. The following week we called to make sure the items arrived at the warehouse and were available to pick up, and we were then told our order was cancelled. We did not cancel our order. We were told that we would receive a phone call back from the manager at the Springfield location to figure out next steps. We never received a phone call back, so instead we called the call center. The call center rep was able to locate our order and confirmed it was not cancelled and that we could pick it up. We still have never received a call back from the manager. We rented a moving truck to pick up our order and brought it back to our new house. When we unboxed it, we noticed the table has been scuffed and glued back in on the side. The sofa’s sidearm was not flush with the back of the sofa, causing the screwed in upholstery to come out. When we called the store, we were told to speak with the escalated store operations. When we called the escalated store operations, Susan told us that when we pick up an item from the distribution center, it’s on us. Bear in mind that when we picked up the items, they were wrapped in boxes and we could not see the damage until we opened them up. Susan said that someone would call us back and then hung up on us. Given Ashley Furniture’s track record of not returning calls, we aren’t holding our breath. We will NEVER EVER purchase from Ashley Furniture again, and will make sure everyone we have ever met hears of our experience.

My sales rep was great. Anyone involved past the point of making the sale could have cared less. Purchased 2 couches, 2 beds & a mattress. Reaching out to the Springfield store directly was near impossible, but luckily my rep gave me his cell number, so he was able to help me & even offered to come in on his day off. Couch was missing a back cushion, so they shipped a replacement to me. Mattress was on backorder, so I was told it would arrive in August (I ordered in June.) I was out of town the last week of July without access to my phone, which is when the mattress came in. I had voicemails beginning July 25 telling me it was ready for pickup & to call to schedule my pickup. I called August 2 when I returned to schedule the pickup. After discussing package dimensions & needing to schedule pickup, the call went blank. The rep wasn't responding to anything, so I hung up. Although I had verified my call back number multiple times "in case the call was disconnected" no one called me back. I then responded to an email from a rep that I had received, letting me know I needed to schedule my pickup by August 7 before they canceled my order. I responded to let them know about the call & let her know I'd be picking up the mattress the following day. The rep responded again, letting me know she would notate the order & extend the pickup window into September since I had originally requested a late pickup due to construction. I went to pick up the mattress, where I was told the mattress wasn't there. The lady at the front desk didn't bother to look into it any further & told me to look up the customer service number and call them. She had zero interest of assisting any further. Couldn't even be bothered to give me the phone number. I called customer service, where I was told the order was still in process & hadn't been delivered to the fulfillment center yet, although I have multiple voicemails telling me my order was available for pickup. I was told it is scheduled to arrive August 5. I drove an hour to pick this up. The representative I spoke with yesterday called me back today to let me know her request to have the mattress delivered to me instead of pickup (since I wasted a trip to Springfield) was denied b/c "after so many days" of me not returning calls, the order was canceled, and I would need to reach out to the store directly again. One week of me not responding to voicemails is all Ashley gives before canceling orders....even though I have an email from an Ashley Rep stating I have until August 7 before my order is canceled. I am completely baffled & disappointed by the level of service, which is next to none, we have received over this order. The only reason I am giving Ashley 2-stars is b/c of the great service Louis provided me. We had every intention of going back for 2 new recliners once construction is done, but this has been the biggest mess.

Where to start? We ordered an unassembled dresser from Ashley in Springfield, MO back in March. When we finally received it from back order in April, it took us over two hours to assemble it because of how poorly it was manufactured. There were serious flaws and some of the bolts given to us to hold the drawers were they need to be, couldn’t even be threaded through. We call the store and they get us in touch with the company we need to call to come out and see if they can fix it or be sent a replacement. They can’t even come until June! June finally comes and they come and say well they can’t fix it and they couldn’t even be paid enough money to put this piece of furniture together because it was essentially a piece of junk. So we wait a few weeks and I go into the store because I have yet to hear from the company. The manager puts in an emergency request to have to company reach out to me regarding our piece of furniture. It’s been almost a month now and I still have yet to hear anything. It’s truly unfortunate because we spent a lot of money on other furniture as well but this experience has been so bad that I will tell everyone I know to stay away. Customer service in the stores is a joke and they don’t even take us seriously.

Bought a new 3 piece sectional about a month ago; paid for in full that day, no financing. The in store experience with the sales rep was fantastic, but everything went to poo after that. They said I'd have the full sectional delivered that following week, yet I only received 1 section. Delivery drivers said another had been there for them to pick up, but the box had been crushed and when they opened they saw it had been damaged so they didn't bring, kudos to them on that part, really. But then they said the third section wasn't even on their list so they weren't sure what was going on with it and customer service would contact me within 48 hours. Never got a call, tried calling for 2 weeks could never get an answer. Finally went through the automated service to see if the pieces were available to schedule another delivery, it said both remaining pieces were ready for delivery. Once again only had one piece delivered today with so sign of the third, and since the missing piece is the live seat that connects the other two pieces I really had nowhere to put the chaise that was brought to me today since I have to have the full couch set up differently in the meantime. Due to this they had to take it back with them and I told them not to deliver until the other piece was also available otherwise it won't fit. Very, very frustrated with the poor communication and customer service from this company right now. Where's the rest of my couch!?

We bought a sofa from them that had a nice delivery team. It came with a rip in the back that they reported and said someone would call us and come patch it. That never happened. Then we paid the couch off and went in for a mattress. We immediately told them we were just looking and made it clear we wanted to be left alone and look for ourselves. Kristen, one of the sales reps was very aggressive in her sales pitches and doesn't let up. She never gave us a moment to think, let alone talk to eachother and never gave us space to look at what we wanted. Instead she was very insistent that we only lay on the literal most expensive mattress in the building and kept avoiding sharing the price. When she shared the cost, she was already doing a mock up of our payments and pressing us to buy right away (total 8k for only the mattress -LOL over the course of 72 months!). We asked for space and she left us alone for literally 30 seconds and was back and doing another sales pitch over our bodies while we tried to relax and think. At one point my partner said he did not want to lay on one of the mattresses while she controlled the remote and she just kept staring at us and waiting without taking a hint. This was the most uncomfortable experience I've ever had. We were actually ready to buy a mattress today and now we will be going somewhere else. As we were leaving, Kristen followed us out yelling after us that no one else sells more mattresses and that they do charity. It was beyond uncomfortable and just kind of disrespectful. I wish these people would learn that we will find them when we are ready and leave us alone. Stop acting like this is a decision you are in on making with us about our finances. You are a sales person looking for a payday, not my family.

We took delivery of damaged from the factory merchandise in October of 2022. A very expensive piece I might add. We were told they would replace it if they couldn't repair it. Three days later material shows up that is not the right material. We report that to Ashley to which they set a Repair appointment for anyway in November. The repair people show up and cannot do the repair because the right material was not sent. Plus the repair person stated this repair would be very difficult to do in my living room. We were told again we would hear from Ashley. A week goes by and we start calling. Through the entire remaining month of November and December we call and leave messages promised the manager would get in contact with us. Finally on 1/3/2023 I showed up at the store and confronted the Store manager. She assures me she will turn in a repair claim but she was having trouble getting a hold of anyone because it was right after the New Year. She told me she would call me the next day to which I never heard from her. So now my wife frustrated goes and confronts her again on 1/26/2023. This time a claim is turned in and again for February and again its cancelled because again the right materials to make the repair have still not been shipped. (We still have the original Material shipped in 2022) We again contact Ashley Home Office and again Customer Service and ANOTHER appointment is set for 4/11/2023. That appointment is too cancelled because again the correct materials have never been sent. Today we tried again three times to contact the store manager at Ashley Home Store on E Independence. Twice we were disconnected and on the 3rd time when we actually got a hold of someone we were intentionally hung up on. Today we filed formal complaints with the Attorney Generals Office, and the Better Business Bureau of SW Missouri.

If you’re looking through negative reviews to see how bad it can get because you’re on the fence, then understand that there are apparently an infinite number of ways a furniture transaction can go wrong and the only thing that Ashley’s is more committed to than producing mediocre furniture is exploring the universe of possibilities of ways that they can fail your expectations. Update: I called the number indicated in the company response below and they said that I was confused by their automated message by understanding it to mean they were looking for additional feedback or to provide additional solutions. That sounds like nonsense taken out of context but believe me it the most sensible thing that has been said by any customer service agent they have. 7/15/23 Update: i don’t recall when exactly I made this original post, but I believe it was in mid or late March. Today is 7/15 and everything is finally done, after dozens of hours, hundreds of calls, emails. Nothing was characteristically different about yesterday versus any other day working with DSG (Ashley furniture Licensee). I was at the location for more than two hours just yesterday after the solution had been submitted, approved, etc. took just that long for the left hand to talk to the right after months of back and forth. I cannot emphasize this enough - this is Spirit Airlines of furniture, and objectively the most dysfunctional organization I have ever worked with, just take up carpentry and make it yourself. You’ll have a skill in the time it takes you to work through their org chart and then you can pass that skill down to your children, who will be long born and resentful of you by the time your issue gets resolved through this company.

We purchased a new bedroom set from Ashley's on black Friday of 2022. We received our nightstands they were damaged, we are almost in February 2023 and we still have not been able to get any assistance on fixing the nightstand or replacing. Our bed was supposed to be delivered before Christmas. We have never received it. No one in customer service had been able to help. About the 2nd week into January we are told that our bedroom furniture has been discontinued, and we cannot get it anymore. We went to the store and we're offered the display model which was dirty from hands and the bottom rails are chipped and the bed is wobbly. We asked for our cash back from purchasing the bed and we were told they would send a check in 6 weeks. We wanted to return the nightstands that don't match any bedroom sets and were told that our $800 nightstands that are damaged we cannot return or receive any refund on. We are extremely upset with the customer service no one at the store wanted to help they kept telling us to call the number. But the number goes to India and they tell us the opposite of what the store says. We had previously bought multiple pieces of furniture from Ashley's and thought they were helpful before but this experience is completely ridiculous

Bad warranty experience and absolutely awful delivery experience! I paid for a 5-year furniture warranty on my six piece dining room set at the time of my original purchase in Sept/Oct 2018. The set was scratched about three years into the warranty; the warranty covered full replacement. After waiting through all of COVID (they wouldn’t come into homes to work during COVID) and then calling back in for a technician to evaluate the furniture again on 10/24/2022, the technician arrived on 12/4/2022 for a ten minute visit/picture session where he stated they needed to replace the entire set. Finally, on 12/28/2022, their delivery company, DSG, brought out the replacement dining room set - two of the four chairs were scratched (they had assembled them in the warehouse and likely scratched them as they pulled them over others’ furniture in an overpacked delivery truck). They installed the table, the other two chairs and a bench. When I told them they needed to replace the two scratched chairs, their delivery supervisor, Rick, insisted all furniture be returned. At the same time, I had Ashley customer service on the phone and they said only return the scratches products for replacements because they said I didn’t need to go back through the technician inspection process which could add another 6-8 weeks to fulfillment. Rick hung up while the Ashley rep was giving direction. The driver then called Rick’s manager, Derek?, and he told his team to remove my newly installed set from the home; I told him, over the phone, I would keep the good pieces and they could replace the damaged items. He insisted his team remove them; I said no way! He then told his team to leave the damaged chairs, which they had already put back into the truck, in my driveway on a sub-freezing blustery day and pull away from my property. The Ashley furniture customer care rep was on the phone with me through the entire ordeal and said she had never heard of something like this before…she agreed it was an awful delivery experience and assured me she would replace the damage chairs and file a complaint against the delivery company, DSG. At this point, I am still awaiting follow-up for replacement of the two damaged chairs. They have not yet satisfactorily completed the delivery and I have not signed for delivery of the order since it remains incomplete. What an awful warranty and delivery service! I asked Rebecca, the Ashley customer care rep, to request an additional 5-year warranty at the expense of DSG to address all the headaches they created in the delivery; I am still awaiting that outcome as well.

On 1.2.22, I ordered living, dining and bedroom sets and was told everything will be in by end of March. With supply chain delays, I got the living and dining furniture in April. Every month, I was told the bedroom set would be coming in 4-6 weeks. In June, I accepted a job in another state and I called the store to get an update on the bedroom set. I was told it would be in by late July, so I scheduled my moving truck for mid-August. The dresser and night stand were in by mid-August. I asked the store to deliver so I could put on the moving truck. The store refused, saying they would not deliver until everything was in. UPDATE: The Reply left to our review included the canned response "contact us at this email/phone number to discuss further". Precisely what I asked them NOT to do. Make me chase you to solve the problem. *** I share this not out of any spite toward the company, but to provide a factual account of our family experience. We ordered several pieces of furniture near the start of June 2021. It is now November 30th. 6 months. We received about 1/2 of our order just before Thanksgiving. We are aware of the supply chain issues brought on by the global pandemic. Those are understood and to be expected, and are mostly out of the local store's control. We get that. What is not understood are problems with the things a store can control thru proper training and self-reflection. I am listing three tips/training items as a suggestion to improve future customers' experience: 1) Always returning phone calls when promised. Sales people need to be trained to give at minimum WEEKLY updates after the initial anticipated delivery schedule is past. There is no reason why a customer needs to be calling to ask "Where's our stuff you said would be here?" 2) Tell the truth, even when it hurts. Continually saying "it'll be here next week" when the salesperson doesn't actually know frustrates the customer, especially when we hear it week after week for months on end. You can control what you tell your customer. All you have to say is, "Honestly Sir/Ma'am, we don't know when it might show up. It could be next week, or it could be a month or two given how other customer's shipments are moving." I can respect someone telling me the unvarnished truth. I do not appreciate "the truck will be here next week...." told to me a half dozen times. It feels like the store is just trying to hold onto my money and are afraid I'll cancel my order if they tell the truth. Maybe they're correct: I won't wait forever, but I'm also going to remember this kind of slimy "hold onto the money" stalling tactic the next time I decide where to go furniture shopping. Business 101: it's not just today's sales that matters. Think about tomorrow / repeat business. 3) Get the act in gear. When I learned several of our pieces of furniture have been sitting in warehouses in St. Louis and Chattanooga for weeks (months?), my question is, "These aren't stuck on a boat or a dock somewhere: why aren't they being delivered?" Amazon trucks are delivering. FedEx trucks are delivering. UPS trucks are delivering. I work for a Fortune 500 company in our Supply Chain division, and our trucks are delivering in 24-48 hours nationwide. Keeping our customers waiting weeks/months for inventory that were sitting in our warehouse is unacceptable. If your fleet of trucks can't get it done, hire one that can. Or worse case scenario, offer the customer a discount and they can pay for UPS/FedEx to go pick it up. Every review should contains Pros as well as Cons, so here are the Pros: The quality of the half of our furniture pieces that we have received is good. The store itself is clean and well laid out. Sales people are knowledgeable about the product itself and are friendly. At the end of the day though, a retailer's #1 job is getting product from the manufacturer to the customer. That is the only reason Retail exists instead of customers directly ordering from the manufacturer. Talking a good game with a nice store and nice sales reps is only 20% of the job. Failing to deliver, inventing fictional timelines, and causing us to chase you for the product we paid for 6 months ago means 2 out of 5 stars is the best I can give. . To whomever Might respond: I don't need to be given your number or email address to send this concern to, nor do I need to be told "we've implemented a program to ensure customer's get their delivery on time." I've seen that same basic, canned response to every review that mentions the same issues I do, and apparently emailing, calling, and your "implemented program" are not working, so I see no need to waste any more time on any of that.

Summary: nearly 3-month delay from when they say furniture will arrive; manager unwilling to waive 10% cancellation fee; serious communication issues; bottom-feeder level customer service. If you'd like to know why I give such a harsh review, please read on. On January 23, 2021, I entered Ashley Homestore Springfield to place an in-person order. After entering the store, I was approached by Home Furnishing Specialist, Ethan Martin. During my visit that day, Ethan verbally gave me estimated delivery dates for the furniture I wanted to purchase as follows: queen bed base - February 4th, loveseat and chair - February 20th, and the sofa - March 9th. On February 11, 2021, I called Ashely Homestore Customer Service and spoke to Josie at 11:25 am. Josie gave me new delivery dates that were, again, different from the ones Ethan had provided on January 23rd. She provided the following delivery dates: queen bed base – February 16th, loveseat – February 23rd, chair – March 9th, and the sofa – April 3rd. On February 21, 2021, I called the company at 12:38pm, only to reach a recording that said the store was closed and to call back during open hours. Then the call disconnected without providing the store hours or allowing me the option of leaving a voicemail message. On April 11, 2021, I called the company at 2:11pm, and was told that the adjustable base was now available for pick-up, but the sofa, loveseat, and chair would be available “the first week of May,” but that could change as the company is at the mercy of the manufacturer. By this point I was no longer interested in completing my purchase with the company and I decided to cancel my order. On April 19, 2021, I called the company at 4:54pm. I reached a receptionist who put me on hold for nearly 4 minutes as she went to get Ethan Martin to speak with me. She returned to the phone to tell me that Ethan was with a customer and asked if he could call me back. I advised that I was entering a 3-hour meeting (5:30-8:30pm) and was not available until after that, at which point the store would be closed. I said I would call back. On April 21, 2021, I called the company at 6:44pm. There was no answer, so I left a voicemail asking for a call back. On April 23, 2021, I called the company at 4:50pm. There was no answer, so I left a voicemail asking for a call back. By April 28, 2021, I still had not received a call back from Ashley Furniture, so I sent an email to their Internal Escalation Team that responds to these negative Google reviews. The email response I got from Brielle with Ashley Furniture on May 1st gave a pat apology for the extensive delay and told me my furniture was now in stock and to contact them to arrange the pick-up. Do you for one second believe a manager of a store doesn't have the ability to cancel an order and waive a cancellation fee? I sure don't.
